Description:
Corner The Future You Want
Featuring spacious, open design and a corner position within a stroll of popular Melville Road, this single storey three bedroom residence is ready to entice a range of buyers. Along with a very generous living room and flowing open kitchen, dining and family domain there's a largely paved courtyard with space to dine alfresco and a front garden filled with roses. Timber cabinetry, great counter space, a gas cooktop, fan forced oven and rangehood fill the practical kitchen with everything needed to whip up delicious meals. Three double bedrooms with built-in robes, a dual entry bathroom, bay windows, ducted heating, split system heating and cooling and an automatic garage confirm appeal. With St Fidelis Primary over the road and Coburg West Primary a stroll away, it's also a short walk to trams, parks, cafes and local shops, and a quick drive can take you to CityLink access and have you in the CBD in next to no time.
Insights: 1 Lever Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
LOCATION IS EVERYTHING!
Purchase off the Plan - Stamp Duty Savings... Condition applies.
Architecturally designed three bedroom townhouse located in the heart of one of Coburg East's best pockets and beautifully positioned opposite McDonald Reserve.
The locale is as convenient as they come, just a leisurely stroll to transport, buzzing Sydney Road, Nicholson Street and a stone's throw away from Coburg High School.
Taking advantage of its street facing orientation and no body corporate attached, this three bedroom offers plush bathrooms, gourmet kitchens, open plan living, garage, off street parking and so much more. The residence is beautifully appointed including, stone bench tops, stainless steel appliances, impressive floor coverings including a combination of quality carpets and pristine tiling.
Development is scheduled for completion April 2018 (approximately)
Feel free to contact Nazih Abbouchi on 0408 588 680 to discuss the plans in the office...

Description:
Instant Style and Park Proximity
In the popular Newlands precinct walking distance to Merri Creek trails and parkland, this distinctive period home provides an environment of immediate quality, comfort and enviable inner-urban convenience. Impeccably presented, the home's inviting interior comprises three bedrooms (master with private ensuite) and stylish central bathroom, open-design living/dining area enhanced by an updated kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances and Bosch dishwasher. Other highlights include ducted heating and split-system a/c, alarm, hardwood floors, large storeroom, plus undercover patio and immaculate backyard garden, front off-street parking for up to three cars. Zoned to Coburg High School, it's also walking distance to Murray Road buses, Coburg Lake and swimming pool, easy access to Nicholson Street trams and Coburg Hill Shopping Centre. Description:
Edwardian Inspired Modern Elegance
A haven of timeless elegance, this Edwardian inspired three bedroom two bathroom townhouse, artfully arranged over three light filled levels promises stylish low maintenance living in the heart of Coburg. Clean lines, superb timber floors and neutral tones enhance the spacious open plan living domain featuring a stylish Franke equipped kitchen with breakfast bar that spills to sunny alfresco dining for effortless indoor/outdoor entertaining. Private bedrooms enjoying leafy views, charismatic raked ceilings and built-in robes provide private retreat for each member of the family and share a modern bathroom, the generous master with box bay window and ensuite. With heating, cooling, separate laundry and car space via ROW with remote, a short walk to Merri Creek parklands and trails, choice of transport, schools, and the vibrant eateries and specialty shopping of Sydney Road, it is sure to delight starters, investors and downsizers alike.

Description:
Space and Style in the Heart of Glencairn
Period charm and extended versatility highlight the appeal of this captivating Californian Bungalow providing an idyllic inner-urban family lifestyle, architecturally designed - just north of Brunswick's border in the tightly-held Glencairn Estate. Beyond its attractive triple-gabled facade, the home's light-filled interior boasts a wide hallway accessing four bedrooms (three with BIRs) and modern central bathroom, open-plan living/dining area with bi-folds revealing a large entertaining deck and delightful backyard garden. Add to this a superb stone-top kitchen with Smeg appliances and walk-in pantry, ducted heating and evaporative cooling, high square-set ceilings throughout, polished floorboards, alarm system, integrated audio, large laundry, plus front off-street parking (gated bluestone-paved driveway). Opposite Mailer Reserve, it's also close to popular schools as well as easy access to Moreland Road buses, Moreland Station, Sydney Road trams, shops and cafes. Exceptional inner-urban family living! In Conjunction with Ian Reid Vendor Advocates

Period Prize with Position and Potential!
Occupying a substantial block of land, this captivating solid-brick Californian presents a lifestyle of immediate quality and comfort along with outstanding options to further enhance and expand (STCA) in a family-focused Coburg neighbourhood. Beyond its gorgeous facade, the home's previously extended interior comprises three bedrooms (large master) all with BIRs, central bathroom and separate powder room, open-design lounge and dining areas complemented by a timber-top kitchen with dishwasher. Description:
Upgrade your Lifestyle
In an idyllic tree-lined street, this stunning town residence invites a superb lifestyle surrounded by an array of exciting lifestyle advantages.
Designed with a stylish contemporary palette, boasting high ceilings, airy light-filled open spaces and luxurious modern features throughout, this residence will impress with a masterful floorplan that flows over three levels.
The ground level provides a sizable 4th bedroom with walk in robe, which with access to the huge remote control four car garage could easily be utilized as a home office scenario.
The entire second level is dedicated to the living zone, with the family/meals area and chef's kitchen with Caesar stone breakfast bar and quality stainless steel appliances extending out to a covered deck and flat grassed yard with gate access to rear laneway, ideal for kids. On the opposite side is the large sun-kissed living room with full length windows and balcony providing delightful views. There's also a powder room and huge laundry on this level
Finally on the top level you have the magnificent master bedroom suite with parents retreat, huge walk in robe, designer ensuite and tree-top balcony views, two further robed bedrooms and a stylish family bathroom.

This charming double fronted Victorian home ticks all the boxes! The home sits in a quiet street and only 10kms from the Melbourne CBD, this is an opportunity not too be missed.
Walking through the home, you will admire the period features throughout, from the polished floorboards to the high ceilings. With a light filled kitchen/meals area incorporating a fire place, stainless steel appliances and an abundance of cupboard and bench space.

Description:
Introducing 'Thelma'
Contemporary features and period styling showcase throughout this stunning single fronted Edwardian home. Solid brick in construction, the home's soaring ceilings and colour palette enhance the generous dimensions of each room. An adorable home in a peaceful pocket on the Brunswick border, the property consists of a street-facing master bedroom with built-in robes, ornamental fireplace and garden views, whilst the expansive central lounge is the ideal space to entertain, or relax in comfort.
The updated kitchen and meals area are light-filled and flow through to the bathroom and laundry, whilst the 2nd bedroom offers additional access to the cottage-style rear garden through French doors. Made comfortable with ducted heating, polished floors, easy to maintain gardens, and fruit trees, potential ROW access and secure garden shed. Conveniently positioned in this prized location only a few minutes walk from Melville Rd tram, Coburg West & St Fidelis Primary Schools, cafes, shops, and offering easy access to the CBD via Citylink.

Description:
Heritage charm, modern comfort
Combining period elegance with contemporary flair, this character-filled two-bedroom Edwardian is located in a prized pocket of Coburg only walking distance from shops, parks and public transport.
The wide hallway with high ceilings, myrtle floorboards and heritage detailing leads to the two bedrooms. The spacious main features split-system heating/cooling and a sunny bay window, while the second includes wall-to-wall built-in robes. Both rooms boast pure-wool carpet, quality block-out, thermal drapes, privacy blinds and panel heating.
The recently renovated bathroom includes an original clawfoot bath, semi-frameless shower screen and European laundry, complemented by the comfort of gas-ducted and electric panel heating.
A large, open-plan living area features Tasmanian oak floors, soaring ceilings and tall windows that combine to create an inviting, light-filled space.
Elegant bi-fold doors open on to a charming al fresco area with established hedging, while the modern kitchen includes stainless-steel appliances and Caesar-stone benchtops.
Other features include five-star, gas-ducted central heating, a monitored alarm system, temperature-controlled gas hot water system, split-system cooling/heating to living area and ROW access via the rear lane.
Only 600m from supermarkets and 650m to Coburg Station, the home is located to take advantage of the amenities and vibrancy of Coburg village.
